        <h1>LeetCode 3381: Maximum Subarray Sum With Length Divisible by K (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an array of integers nums and an integer k. Return the maximum sum of a non-empty subarray of nums, such that the size of the subarray is divisible by k. A subarray is a contiguous non-empty sequence of elements within an array.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,2], k = 1<br/>
                Output: 3<br/>
                Explanation: The subarray [1, 2] with sum 3 has length equal to 2 which is divisible by 1.<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [-1,-2,-3,-4,-5], k = 4<br/>
                Output: -10<br/>
                Explanation: The maximum sum subarray is [-1, -2, -3, -4] with sum -10 and length 4 which is divisible by 4.<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [-5,1,2,-3,4], k = 2<br/>
                Output: 4<br/>
                Explanation: The maximum sum subarray is [1, 2, -3, 4] with sum 4 and length 4 which is divisible by 2.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    long long maxSubarraySum(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector&lt;long long&gt; prefixSum(n + 1, 0);
        
        // Calculate prefix sums
        for (int i = 0; i &lt; n; i++) {
            prefixSum[i + 1] = prefixSum[i] + nums[i];
        }
        
        long long maxSum = LLONG_MIN;
        
        // For each remainder class (0 to k-1)
        for (int remainder = 0; remainder &lt; k; remainder++) {
            long long minPrefix = LLONG_MAX;
            
            // Check all indices with the same remainder when divided by k
            for (int i = remainder; i &lt;= n; i += k) {
                if (minPrefix != LLONG_MAX) {
                    maxSum = max(maxSum, prefixSum[i] - minPrefix);
                }
                minPrefix = min(minPrefix, prefixSum[i]);
            }
        }
        
        return maxSum;
    }
};</code></pre>
